 :tx/rationale "AUDIT ARCH-LOOPS: Loop analysis — 4 tight, 3 open, 2 broken, 2 phantom loops identified. OBSERVATION: TIGHT LOOPS (working): (1) Transact->LIVE->Query — datom inserted, LIVE updated, query reads current state. Healthy. (2) Observe->Store->Seed->Agent — knowledge captured, stored, assembled into seed for next session. The core hypothesis loop, working. (3) Hypothesis->Outcome->Calibration — prediction at harvest, actual at task close, mean error computed, weights adjusted. Working but degrading (mean error 0.521, trend degrading). (4) Bilateral Scan->Gap Detection->Task Creation — scans detect gaps, gaps surface as tasks, tasks completed. Working. OPEN LOOPS (data produced not consumed): (1) Compiler-generated proptests — compiler.rs generates test code but no pipeline executes it. NEG-010 violation. (2) 123 uncrystallized observations — captured but never promoted to spec elements. Pipeline stalls at crystallize step. (3) Merge cascade stubs — 3/5 steps are no-ops, merge receipt notes what should cascade but actions not implemented. BROKEN LOOPS (feedback path severed): (1) Access log significance — AS-007 specifies Hebbian significance via access log, budget module has ActivationStrategy types but access log not implemented. Queries happen, significance not accumulated. (2) Confusion signal -> re-ASSOCIATE — INV-SIGNAL-002 specifies confusion triggers re-association, signal types exist but pipeline not wired. PHANTOM LOOPS (appear closed, feedback is no-op): (1) F(S)->Guidance->Agent — F(S) computed and displayed but no automated response to changes. Agent sees number, no corrective action triggered. (2) Hypothesis calibration->weight adjustment — calibrate_boundary_weights() computes WeightAdjustment but adjusted weights not automatically transacted back. SIGNIFICANCE: 7 open/broken/phantom loops. NEG-010 says every loop must close. These are the system's current learning-loop debt."
